WEBVTT

00:00:01.550 --> 00:00:06.549
I'd like to talk about a very common expression in the Bible.

00:00:06.549 --> 00:00:11.550
The expression is, I am with you.

00:00:11.550 --> 00:00:16.550
13 times, it's attributed to a statement from Jehovah.

00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:22.550
Three times, it's something that Jesus said to one or more of His disciples.

00:00:22.550 --> 00:00:30.550
Of course, there are dozens of other times that the same sentiment is expressed using similar wording.

00:00:31.550 --> 00:00:38.549
Few things in the world equal the joy humans experience than the birth of a child.

00:00:38.549 --> 00:00:47.549
As children grow up, they are sometimes exposed to situations that tend to cause nervousness or even fear.

00:00:47.549 --> 00:00:56.549
So a parent may occasionally feel compelled to reassure a child, have no fear, I am with you.

00:00:56.549 --> 00:01:02.859
Jehovah loves His servants as if they were His children.

00:01:02.859 --> 00:01:09.859
Likewise, at John 13, one, Jesus' feelings for His disciples are well expressed.

00:01:09.859 --> 00:01:18.859
There it says, Jesus, having loved His own who were in the world, loved them to the end.

00:01:19.859 --> 00:01:33.859
So when we face fears, trials or causes for anxiety, both our Heavenly Father and His Son, Jesus, we assuredly say, I am with you.

00:01:33.859 --> 00:01:36.859
Think of the righteous man, Noah.

00:01:36.859 --> 00:01:41.859
Genesis 6.9 says that Noah walked with the true God.

00:01:41.859 --> 00:01:45.859
There's no doubt that Jehovah was with Noah.

00:01:45.859 --> 00:01:49.859
He preserved Him and His family through the flood.

00:01:49.859 --> 00:01:54.859
Afterward, Jehovah further proved He was with Noah.

00:01:54.859 --> 00:02:00.859
In Genesis 9, Jehovah said, I am now establishing my covenant with you.

00:02:00.859 --> 00:02:06.859
Never again will all flesh be destroyed by the waters of a flood.

00:02:06.859 --> 00:02:13.860
Jehovah could have made that determination and promised Himself that He wouldn't do that again.

00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:26.860
But instead, He reached out to Noah and reassured Him that He was with Him by making the rainbow covenant with Noah and His offspring.

00:02:26.860 --> 00:02:38.860
Using similar terminology, Jehovah indicated that He was with Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, Joseph, Moses, Joshua and Gideon.

00:02:38.860 --> 00:02:47.860
They were all individuals that Jehovah was pleased with, so He reassured them He was with them.

00:02:47.860 --> 00:02:50.860
How about a group of people?

00:02:50.860 --> 00:02:57.860
Is Jehovah moved to feel the same way toward a large crowd of His servants collectively?

00:02:57.860 --> 00:03:05.139
Please find with me Exodus 6, verse 6 and 7.

00:03:05.139 --> 00:03:15.990
The whole nation of Israel was experiencing severe trials and suffering as slaves in Egypt.

00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:20.990
Notice Jehovah's reassurance to the fast number of people.

00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:41.990
Verse 6 and 7, state, therefore, say to the Israelites, I am Jehovah and I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians and rescue you from their slavery and I will reclaim you with an outstretched arm and with great judgments.

00:03:41.990 --> 00:03:53.990
And I will take you in as my people and I will be your God and you will certainly know that I am Jehovah your God who is bringing you out from under the burdens of Egypt.

00:03:53.990 --> 00:04:02.990
If that great mixed group of people would follow His leadings, He said He'd take them in, He would be their God.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:06.990
What was He saying? He was reassuring them.

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:09.990
I will be with you.

00:04:09.990 --> 00:04:26.990
And He was, for 40 years in the wilderness, He was with them, feeding them, providing water for them, ensuring their clothes and sandals would not weigh out, protecting them from poisonous snakes and so forth.

00:04:26.990 --> 00:04:34.990
And later, when entering the land of promise, He protected them during enemy warfare.

00:04:34.990 --> 00:04:44.990
Jehovah promised to be with and to support the kings of Israel as long as they heeded His commandments and direction.

00:04:44.990 --> 00:04:54.990
King Solomon was told, Jehovah, you God will not desert you or abandon you but He will be with you.

00:04:54.990 --> 00:05:05.620
King Asa was informed, Jehovah is with you as long as you remain with Him.

00:05:05.620 --> 00:05:16.620
When faced with overwhelming enemy forces, King Jehosephat was told, tomorrow go out against them and Jehovah will be with you.

00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:26.899
Jehovah also proved to be with the many prophets that he sent out in his name, just one example is Jeremiah.

00:05:26.899 --> 00:05:42.899
Imagine if you had Jeremiah's assignment, suppose you had been directed to deliver a scathing denunciation and judgment against wicked kings, corrupt priests and false prophets, how would you feel?

00:05:42.899 --> 00:05:51.899
Underqualified? Would you feel like a little child challenging a whole group of evil grown-ups?

00:05:51.899 --> 00:06:01.899
Notice how Jeremiah felt as he expressed himself at Jeremiah chapter 1 verse 6.

00:06:01.899 --> 00:06:10.899
But I said, alas or so in Lord Jehovah, I do not know how to speak for I am just a boy.

00:06:10.899 --> 00:06:15.899
What were Jehovah's reassuring words in reply?

00:06:15.899 --> 00:06:25.899
Jeremiah 1, 8 and 9, do not be afraid because of their appearance for I am with you to save you, declares Jehovah.

00:06:25.899 --> 00:06:34.899
Then Jehovah stretched out his hand and touched my mouth and Jehovah said to me, I have put my words in your mouth.

00:06:34.899 --> 00:06:43.899
If Jehovah put the words that you were to say in your mouth, you'd no longer feel like a little child, would you?

00:06:44.899 --> 00:06:51.899
We don't think of Jeremiah as being an incredible Superman, he was a human like us.

00:06:51.899 --> 00:07:01.899
It's of interest that though Jeremiah lived in another time and place, he faced situations similar to those we face.

00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:11.899
We interact with different types of people in our daily life at work and at school, some of them can be intimidating.

00:07:11.899 --> 00:07:18.899
And like Jeremiah, Jehovah has commissioned us to go to strangers and preach.

00:07:18.899 --> 00:07:21.899
We share the good news of the kingdom.

00:07:21.899 --> 00:07:26.899
Some are interested, others are just plain apathetic.

00:07:26.899 --> 00:07:33.899
But at times we may come across someone who is angry and may even be threatening.

00:07:33.899 --> 00:07:37.899
This is the time to remember Jeremiah.

00:07:38.899 --> 00:07:47.899
Though initially timid, he courageously faced the challenge of an intimidating response.

00:07:47.899 --> 00:07:50.899
How did he rally to the occasion?

00:07:50.899 --> 00:07:57.899
It was because Jehovah had reassured him, I am with you.

00:07:57.899 --> 00:08:04.240
He said, I have put my words in your mouth.

00:08:04.240 --> 00:08:08.240
Does Jehovah do something similar for us?

00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:09.240
Yes.

00:08:09.240 --> 00:08:17.240
Long after Jeremiah and the other faithful ones that were recorded in the Hebrew Scriptures came and went,

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:24.490
Jehovah has proved to be with true Christians both past and present.

00:08:24.490 --> 00:08:27.490
Find with me John chapter 8.

00:08:27.490 --> 00:08:32.820
Think of Jesus.

00:08:32.820 --> 00:08:38.820
It's true he was a perfect man, but did Jehovah leave him all alone?

00:08:38.820 --> 00:08:43.820
Did John 816, what did Jesus himself say?

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:53.820
